
context is a small structure of data that provides additional info that
can help organize the data it connects to.

this will include any date/time info associated with the source.
created, modified, etc.

also included is the id of the creating entity or source of the text.
the type of class of document is part of context.

the text of the source will be summarized with three specific actions:
1. certain words will be removed ( see a typical deleted words list )
2. repeated words will be highlighted
3. targeted words will be highlighted ( there will be a list )

write a job that creates the context data from a chunk of text. perhaps
it should refine context based on the given text, then it could be used
on consecutive refinements of a text file.  as a text file is broken down
into its components the context can be refined.  this would help with tabli
files and jump cut files that contain a variety of chunks of text.

context data should include a weight for the various elements which should help
with refinements. the size of the document being analyzed will help to modify
the weight  based on ratio and steps in size at each refinement.

if the parent was a container and the current is a container then weights
will be reduced considerably where there is no match.  if the current item
is not a container then there will be no reduction of the parent context.
